A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO LANDSCAPE ARCHITECTS.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the State's board of
2 professional engineers, architects, surveyors, and landscape
3 architects (board) previously voted in favor of adopting the
4 Uniform Licensure Standard for Landscape Architecture developed
5 in 2022 by the Council of Landscape Architectural Registration
6 Boards, of which the board is a member. The Council of
7 Landscape Architectural Registration Boards is a nonprofit
8 organization that works to protect the public’s health, safety,
9 and welfare by establishing and promoting professional licensure
10 standards for landscape architects. Its members are the
11 licensure boards across the United States and Canada.
12 The legislature further finds that the board is the entity
13 best suited to determine the eligibility requirements for the
14 licensure of landscape architects in the State and should be
15 authorized to implement standards as it deems appropriate.
16 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to:
2026-2521 SB2607 CDl SMA.docx 1
iHiiHiiiimiHiniiiiiiiiii

Page 2
S.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 (1) Authorize the board of professional engineers,
2 architects, surveyors, and landscape architects to
3 determine the appropriate educational and examination
4 requirements for landscape architect licensure in the
5 State; and
6 (2) Clarify experience requirements for landscape
7 architect licensure.
8 SECTION 2. Section 464-1, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
9 amended by adding a new definition to be appropriately inserted
10 and to read as follows:
11 ’"’Board” means the board of professional engineers,
12 architects, surveyors, and landscape architects established in
13 section 464-6.”
14 SECTION 3. Section 464-8, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
15 amended to read as follows:
